          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "CYCLO"
                ],
                "institute": "3CZRUJF"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The experiment was carried out with a",
                "momentum-analyzed 25.83 MeV 3He beam (from the U-120M",
                "isochronous cyclotron at the Nuclear  Physics",
                "Institute of the Czech Academy of Sciences)"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Neon gas target. The target gas cell contained high-",
                "purity isotopic  20Ne (99.99%). The body of the target",
                "gas cell had a cylindrical shape  with an inner",
                "diam. of 104 mm and an inner height of 20 mm. Input",
                "and output windows were made from 3.05-mu-m-thick Havar",
                "foils. The working pressure was kept at 195 mbar and",
                "was monitored by a gas  control system, which",
                "continuously monitored the pressure and  temperature",
                "of the gas inside the chamber."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The charge collection by the Faraday cup"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SIBAR",
                "SILI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "  Telescopes consisting of 220-mu-m",
                "Si surface barrier  detectors and 4-mm-thick Si(Li)",
                "detectors. Both telescopes were equipped with a  pair",
                "of collimating slits of dimension 2 mm x 3 mm.",
                "One telescope was fixed at the angle of 19 degr. as a",
                "monitor, and the second one was moved during the",
                "measurement between lab. angl. of 6.5 and 70. degr."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-SYS",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The systematic uncertainty that was due to",
                "the effective target  thickness and detector solid",
                "angle, which are correlated, was estimated to be 8%.",
                "An additional uncertainty of 3% was estimated for the",
                "charge collection by the Faraday cup."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The total uncertainty, which includes",
                "systematic and statistical uncertainties, was",
                "estimated to be mostly less than 10%"
              ]
            }
